.TH ClickKey 3X
.SH NAME
\*LClickKey \*O\(em Convenience routine to press and release a key.
.SH SYNOPSIS
\*LClickKey\*O
\*V[ModifierList]* Key\*O
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
\*LClickKey\*O
command will simulate the clicking of any key on the standard keyboard,
including Motif Virtual Keys.
The key click maybe modified by any combination of the standard X modifiers.
This function usually follows a command to
\*LLocatePointer\*O to a widget which accepts keyboard input. The key
click is composed of a key press immediately followed by a key release. 
.IP "\*V[ModifierList]*\*O" 10n
List of Modifiers to modify the key click. For a full list of available
Modifiers see \*LModifierList(3X)\*O. Default is no modifiers.
.IP "\*VKey\*O"
Key to be clicked. For a full list of available Keys see \*LKeyList(3X)\*O.
.SH EXAMPLE
\*LClickKey <Shift> KPageDown\*O
.PP
This will click the KPageDown key with the modifier Shift.
.PP 
For more information about \*LClickKey\*O, see
the \*EOSF/Motif Quality Assurance Test Suite User's Guide\*O.
.PP
.SH "RELATED INFORMATION"
